essential features
------------------
gods
  orcus                           (black)
    - firebolt
    - emergency teleport
    - limited levitation
  surt, the fire giant            (orange)
    - firebolt
    - immunity to fire and lava
    - damage +10%
    - speed -20%
  ares, god of war                (red)
    - firebolt
    - damage +20%
    - speed +20%
    - limited levitation per level
  morrigan, the demon queen       (blue)
    - fast missile
    - limited wraithwalk per level
    - magical armour 1d20
    - speed +50%
  - lilith                        (white)
  - loviater                      (yellow)
    - darknes
  - horned god                    (green)
  sacrificing an acolyte of the same god - bad

domains
  - dungeon
  - swamp, explosive bogs
  - nethervoid
  - graveyard
  - underhell
abilities
  - keep a percentage of money or stats each time you restart
  - madness as an ability - randomly fire a spell
  - bloodfeaster - each corpse can be drained / chance of resurrecting something much stronger
  - lightbringer - light follows you randomly
  - demonbloodpact - vow to not hurt demons
  - breathless - gas weapons have no effect
  - wraithwalk - walk into walls
  - take on limitations at start e.g one leg, limited jump, reduced spell cost
  - levitation essential for chasms and return trip
weapon slots
  - etherblast to hit ghosts in walls
  - emergency teleport
gameplay
  - hard coded to fire fireball
  - traps must do something / gas effects
  - items can be lost in deep water
  - chests need to contain something and those items destroyed when the chest is
  - spell points to collect
  - spells need to have a cost that can be influenced by specializing
  - boss that can move levels
  - projectile collision with projectile
  - boulders that can crush
  - cobwebs burns and get you stuck
  - ice weapon and shattering
  - intelligent monsters when hurt should escape
  - shrines that reduce spell points
  - bushes quiver when monster is behind? / items hiding in bushes 
  - anti magic areas
  - anti anti magic areas
monsters
  - ogri - like in Doctor Who, monoliths that move slowly and block the way
  - unihulk
  - ravenbeast
  - bearowl
  - ogyr (celtic)
  - door mimic
  - thief that can steal items
allies
  - Allies vanish each level and the life force is returned to you
  - Life force can be applied to the summoning of allies each level.
    Each ally that dies in-level, is a permanent loss of life force.
    Hence you need to balance how many allies to summon with the chance
    of permanent loss.
ui
  - replay seed
  - play weekly/daily seed - generated from date
  - random player name e.g. galatrex the dark

